      "content": {
        "title": "Accumulation Functions",
        "definition": "Functions defined by F(x) = ∫_a^x f(t) dt whose values represent accumulated quantity from a fixed lower limit to x.",
        "summary": "Accumulation functions model running totals and their derivatives recover the instantaneous rate being accumulated."
      },
